msgid "Client Templates"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/clients/client-templates.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you have a lot of applications you need to secure and register within your organization it can become quite tedious\n"
"to configure the <<_protocol-mappers, protocol mappers>>\n"
"and <<_client_scope, scope>> for each of these clients.  {project_name} allows you to define shared client configuration in an entity called a _client template_.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/clients/client-templates.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "To create a client template, go to the `Client Templates` left menu item.  This initial screen shows you a list of currently defined templates.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/clients/client-templates.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To create a template click the `Create` button.  This brings you to a simple screen in which you name the template and hit save.\n"
"A _client template_ will have similar tabs to regular clients.  You'll be able to define <<_protocol-mappers, protocol mappers>>\n"
"and <<_client_scope, scope>> which can be inherited by other clients.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/clients/client-templates.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Having a client inherit from a template is as simple as choosing the template from the `Client Template` drop down list on either the\n"
"`Add Client` or client `Settings` tab.  You will see the `Mappers` and `Scope` tabs get additional switches which allow you\n"
"to turn on or off inheriting from the parent template.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/clients/client-templates.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Future versions of client templating may get more inheritable configuration options, but for now, that's all there is to talk about.\n"
msgstr ""
